# Convention / ledger files: append-only shared docs that many parallel agents
# update (HQ's convention tells every agent to update docs/BACKLOG.md). The
# `union` merge driver auto-resolves append collisions by keeping BOTH sides, so
# two branches that each add a backlog entry never conflict — while real code
# conflicts still surface normally. HQ's own merge (clone → git merge → push)
# honours this; the GitHub merge API does not.
#
# Only ever apply `union` to genuinely append-only ledgers — NEVER to files whose
# existing lines get edited (union would keep both versions of an edited line).
docs/BACKLOG.md merge=union
